    </td></tr>
    <tr><td style=3D"padding:0 24px 4px 24px;">
      <h3 style=3D"margin:0;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Geneva,Verdana,sans=
-serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:#1B1B3A;line-height:1.4;">Prompt-=
Chained Triage</h3>
      <p style=3D"margin:4px 0 0 0;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Geneva,Verda=
na,sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:#888888;">Step-by-step agent reasoning ins=
tead of single-shot prompts</p>
    </td></tr>
    <tr><td style=3D"padding:16px 24px 24px 24px;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahom=
a,Geneva,Verdana,sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#444444;line-height:1.7;">
      <p style=3D"margin:0 0 14px 0;">
        <strong>Why single-shot fails:</strong> When you ask an LLM to "analy=
ze this and tell me what to do," it tries to be helpful all at once. The resu=
lt is broad but shallow &#8212; it summarizes but doesn't truly classify, it =
suggests but doesn't cross-reference, it answers but doesn't catch what's mis=
sing.
      </p>
      <p style=3D"margin:0 0 14px 0;">
        <strong>The pattern:</strong> Decompose the task into a chain of disc=
rete prompts. Each step has a single job and produces a structured output tha=
t feeds the next step. The agent follows a deliberate reasoning path.
      </p>

      <table role=3D"presentation" width=3D"100%" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspaci=
ng=3D"0" border=3D"0" style=3D"margin:0 0 16px 0;background:#F0F6FF;border:1p=
x solid #C8DDF5;border-radius:6px;">
        <tr><td style=3D"padding:16px 20px;font-family:Consolas,'Courier New'=
,monospace;font-size:13px;color:#0078D4;line-height:2.0;text-align:center;">
          Step 1: Read input &#8594; extract structured fields<br>
          <span style=3D"color:#999;">&#8595;</span><br>
          Step 2: Generate scoped search queries<br>
          <span style=3D"color:#999;">&#8595;</span><br>
          Step 3: Search sources &#8594; aggregate context<br>
          <span style=3D"color:#999;">&#8595;</span><br>
          Step 4: Classify type + assess completeness<br>
          <span style=3D"color:#999;">&#8595;</span><br>
          Step 5: Recommend actions with evidence
        </td></tr>
      </table>

