<!-- PATTERN BREAKDOWN: PLAYBOOK ORCHESTRATION -->
<tr><td class=3D"content-block" style=3D"padding:0 32px 24px 32px;">
  <table role=3D"presentation" width=3D"100%" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=
=3D"0" border=3D"0" style=3D"border-left:4px solid #0078D4;background:#FAFAFA=
;border-radius:0 6px 6px 0;">
    <tr><td style=3D"padding:20px 24px 12px 24px;">
      <h2 style=3D"margin:0;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Geneva,Verdana,sans=
-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#0078D4;letter-spacing:1.5px;text=
-transform:uppercase;">&#129513; Pattern Breakdown: Part B</h2>
    </td></tr>
    <tr><td style=3D"padding:0 24px 4px 24px;">
      <h3 style=3D"margin:0;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Geneva,Verdana,sans=
-serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:#1B1B3A;line-height:1.4;">Playboo=
k-Driven Orchestration</h3>
      <p style=3D"margin:4px 0 0 0;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Geneva,Verda=
na,sans-serif;font-size:12px;color:#888888;">Separate what to do (YAML) from =
how to execute (agent)</p>
    </td></tr>
    <tr><td style=3D"padding:16px 24px 24px 24px;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahom=
a,Geneva,Verdana,sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#444444;line-height:1.7;">
      <p style=3D"margin:0 0 14px 0;">
        <strong>The problem prompt chaining creates:</strong> Once you have a=
 multi-step reasoning chain, someone needs to define and maintain those steps=
. If the process logic is hardcoded in the agent, only developers can change =
it. The customer's process owners &#8212; the people who actually know the tr=
iage rules &#8212; are locked out.
      </p>
      <p style=3D"margin:0 0 14px 0;">
        <strong>The pattern:</strong> Define the prompt chain in a YAML playb=
ook. The playbook describes <em>what</em> steps to execute and what each step=
 should produce. The agent's orchestration layer handles <em>how</em> &#8212;=
 executing prompts, passing context between steps, managing errors. This sepa=
ration means:
      </p>

      <table role=3D"presentation" width=3D"100%" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspaci=
ng=3D"0" border=3D"0" style=3D"margin:0 0 16px 0;background:#F0F6FF;border:1p=
x solid #C8DDF5;border-radius:6px;">
        <tr><td style=3D"padding:16px 20px;font-family:Consolas,'Courier New'=
,monospace;font-size:13px;color:#0078D4;line-height:1.8;">
          <strong style=3D"font-family:'Segoe UI',sans-serif;color:#1B1B3A;">=
Playbook (YAML) &#8212; owned by process team</strong><br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;step_1: Read work item, extract fields<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;step_2: Search {sources} for {keywords}<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;step_3: Classify into {categories}<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;step_4: Generate recommendations<br>
          <br>
          <strong style=3D"font-family:'Segoe UI',sans-serif;color:#1B1B3A;">=
Agent orchestrator &#8212; owned by engineering</strong><br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;Executes steps, chains context, handles errors
        </td></tr>
      </table>

      <p style=3D"margin:0 0 10px 0;"><strong>Why CSAs should lead with this:=
</strong></p>
      <table role=3D"presentation" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" border=
=3D"0" style=3D"margin:0 0 14px 0;">
        <tr><td style=3D"padding:4px 0;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Geneva,V=
erdana,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#444444;line-height:1.5;">
          <span style=3D"color:#0078D4;font-weight:bold;">&#8226;</span>&nbsp=
; <strong>New process?</strong> New playbook. No code changes, no dev sprints.
        </td></tr>
        <tr><td style=3D"padding:4px 0;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Geneva,V=
erdana,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#444444;line-height:1.5;">
          <span style=3D"color:#0078D4;font-weight:bold;">&#8226;</span>&nbsp=
; <strong>Multiple teams?</strong> Each team gets their own playbook. Same ag=
ent.
        </td></tr>
        <tr><td style=3D"padding:4px 0;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Geneva,V=
erdana,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#444444;line-height:1.5;">
          <span style=3D"color:#0078D4;font-weight:bold;">&#8226;</span>&nbsp=
; <strong>Governance?</strong> Playbooks are versionable, reviewable, auditab=
le &#8212; like any config file.
        </td></tr>
        <tr><td style=3D"padding:4px 0;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Geneva,V=
erdana,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#444444;line-height:1.5;">
          <span style=3D"color:#0078D4;font-weight:bold;">&#8226;</span>&nbsp=
; <strong>Demos?</strong> Swap playbooks to show different scenarios without =
rebuilding anything.
        </td></tr>
      </table>

      <table role=3D"presentation" width=3D"100%" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspaci=
ng=3D"0" border=3D"0" style=3D"background:#F0ECF5;border-radius:6px;">
        <tr><td style=3D"padding:12px 16px;font-family:'Segoe UI',Tahoma,Gene=
va,Verdana,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#444444;line-height:1.6;">
          <strong style=3D"color:#6B2FA0;">Customer conversation starter:</st=
rong> "What if your process owners could define how the agent handles request=
s &#8212; without filing a dev ticket every time the rules change?"
        </td></tr>
      </table>
    </td></tr>
  </table>
</td></tr>

